  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "[PERM] Industry Partnership for Higher Education industry)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Build and manage industry partnerships to create internships, placements, collaborations, and fundraising opportunities.</li><li>Source and secure new partners, maintain long-term relationships, and manage MOUs and agreements.</li><li>Act as the main liaison between industry partners, university leadership, faculty, students, alumni, and internal teams.</li><li>Develop industry engagement strategies, conduct market and employer analysis, and position company as a premium engineering talent source.</li><li>Plan and execute career and industry engagement events, including talks, networking sessions, and employer visits.</li><li>Collaborate with alumni, academic teams, student groups, and marketing to enhance employer engagement and visibility.</li><li>Track partnerships, placements, and engagement outcomes; provide insights, reports, and strategic recommendations.</li><li>Represent company at industry events and conferences.</li><li>Engage in continuous professional development and share best practices internally.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree with 5+ years of relevant experience in corporate partnerships or career services (7+ years for Manager level).</li><li>Proven track record in securing industry partnerships and delivering measurable\noutcomes.</li><li>Strong stakeholder engagement, negotiation, communication, and analytical skills.</li><li>Confident working in cross-cultural environments; proactive, adaptable, and\nteam-oriented.</li><li>IT proficient and able to manage multiple priorities under pressure.</li></ul><p></p><p>Please state your availability, current and expected salary in the resume.</p><p><br />We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. </p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd   |   EA Licence: 11C3793   |  Eddie Tang |   Registration No: R1221129</p>",
